#!hexa strict

// @resolver-bypass(reason="darwin-native HXC A24 v2 bounded n-gram + class-gate first-tick (F-A24-3 latency retraction option a+b combined)")
// @tool(slug="hxc-a24-v2-bounded", desc="HXC algorithm A24 v2: BOUNDED n-gram grammar induction with class-gate first-tick (F-A24-3 latency retraction option a+b combined). v1 (^X, fc1160b3) tripped F-A24-3 hard: 75.9% files (164/216) hit 5s timeout; 39KB JSON took 40+ seconds (>1000ms/KB) due to PASS 1 O(N×L×K) n-gram scan with K=65000 unique × 6 lengths = 390K candidate sort. v2 attacks 4 axes simultaneously: (1) drop A24_NGRAM_LENGTHS_v2 to {3,4} only (6→2 lengths, 3x scan reduction); (2) raise A24_MIN_BYTES_v2 to 1024 (raw 142 D2 pre-gate; below 1KB always identity passthrough); (3) hard-cap A24_MAX_INPUT_BYTES_v2 at 65536 (above 64KB always identity to bound K); (4) hard-cap A24_MAX_NGRAMS_v2 at 4096 (cap K, bound O(K²) sort to 16M ops worst-case). NEW sigil ^[ (post-A19 ^Z, A24 v1 ^X). raw 137 cmix-ban MAINTAINED: integer-only deterministic n-gram + greedy frequency-saving rule selection, NOT cmix-class. raw 91 honest C3 first-tick scope: PASS 1 (bounded scan) + PASS 2 (a24v2_build with K-cap) + PASS 2.5 (in-sample estimator) + PASS 3 (5 fixtures + 3 latency probes) + PASS 4 LIVE FIRE deferred to subsequent tick.")
// @usage(hexa /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/self/stdlib/hxc_a24_v2_bounded.hexa --selftest)
// @usage(hexa /Users/ghost/core/hexa-lang/self/stdlib/hxc_a24_v2_bounded.hexa build <in>)
// @exit_codes(0=ok, 1=selftest-fail, 2=io-error, 3=bad-args)
//
// First-tick scope (raw 91 honest C3):
//
//   PASS 1 — bounded n-gram scan spec
//     A24_NGRAM_LENGTHS_v2 = {3, 4} only (drop 2, 5, 6, 8 — 6 lengths → 2 lengths,
//     3x scan-cost reduction). Length-2 is too short to save anything (marker+id=3
//     bytes already exceeds L=2 raw bytes). Length-5/6/8 contribute marginal
//     coverage on JSON-heavy at heavy O(K) cost.
//     A24_MIN_BYTES_v2 = 1024 (raw 142 D2 pre-gate). Below 1KB the rule-table
//     overhead always exceeds savings on first-tick wire — identity passthrough.
//     A24_MAX_INPUT_BYTES_v2 = 65536 (hard cap). Above 64KB unique n-gram count
//     K grows beyond budget; identity passthrough preserves byte-eq invariant
//     while bounding wallclock to known-finite budget.
