//     16M ops worst-case → ≤500ms wallclock budget honored).
//     A24_LATENCY_BUDGET_MS = 500 (hard wallclock cap; over budget → revert
//     to identity). Implemented structurally via the input-byte hard cap +
//     n-gram count hard cap, NOT via runtime check (hexa interp time_now_ms
//     not reliably available in this build).
//
//   PASS 2 — a24v2_build (bounded n-gram scan + greedy rule selection)
//     For each L in {3, 4}, single forward sweep building {ngram → count} map.
//     CAP enforcement: stop inserting new keys once map size reaches
//     A24_MAX_NGRAMS_v2 (4096); existing keys keep counting. K bounded.
//     Candidates filtered by saving > 0 AND count ≥ A24_MIN_FREQ. Sorted by
//     saving descending (insertion sort over post-filter set, typically ≪ K).
//     Greedy non-overlapping rule selection bounded by _rule_budget_v2(n).
//
